WEBVTT

00:21.570 --> 00:22.271
What are you doing?

00:23.732 --> 00:24.433
Planting this tree.

00:25.955 --> 00:27.316
Right, that's a small tree.

00:27.336 --> 00:28.297
Yeah, it'll get bigger.

00:29.318 --> 00:29.959
Tomorrow?

00:31.741 --> 00:32.482
No, not tomorrow.

00:33.703 --> 00:34.224
Wind then.

00:35.925 --> 00:37.287
Long after I'm gone.

00:39.049 --> 00:39.529
Many years.

00:40.651 --> 00:45.175
Maybe by the time you get to be my age, it'll be big enough to provide shade.

00:46.297 --> 00:47.538
Well, that's not fair.

00:49.474 --> 00:51.736
Do you enjoy swinging on the rope in your yard?

00:52.877 --> 00:53.658
Yeah.

00:53.678 --> 00:56.361
Who planted that tree?

00:56.381 --> 00:58.223
Uh...

00:58.243 --> 01:00.225
It's always been there.

01:00.245 --> 01:00.445
No.

01:01.406 --> 01:08.353
That tree was planted by someone generations ago so that you could play in its shade.

01:10.735 --> 01:11.496
I'm just doing the same.

01:11.976 --> 01:13.698
Well, bugs live in it, squirrels.

01:14.459 --> 01:17.522
Yes, yeah, but when it's big and it'll be a home,

01:18.338 --> 01:19.640
for all the wildlife.

01:21.482 --> 01:22.663
Who are water in a tree?

01:22.984 --> 01:23.324
I will.

01:25.707 --> 01:26.308
Do you want to help?

01:27.349 --> 01:27.770
Yeah.

01:30.593 --> 01:35.099
All right, here you go.

01:36.701 --> 01:38.343
All right, let's go over here.

01:39.945 --> 01:41.026
Got water all the way around.

01:43.509 --> 01:44.210
That's good.

02:43.874 --> 02:45.056
Welcome to the Well Community Church.

02:45.076 --> 02:46.758
So glad you're hanging out with us here this week.

02:46.798 --> 02:49.743
If we have not had the privilege of meeting yet, my name's Brad.

02:50.263 --> 02:52.306
I'd like to share with you a little bit about what's happening.

02:52.326 --> 03:01.199
It's been a very interesting season here at the Well, and we are taking some next steps that we just want to make sure everybody is aware of as we move forward.

03:01.219 --> 03:06.126
I met a couple here today here for the first time, and I said, you know, it's a really interesting time to come.

03:06.267 --> 03:11.314
Some would argue it's a terrible time because we are launching a capital campaign, but honestly,

03:11.426 --> 03:12.348
I want to reframe that.

03:12.388 --> 03:14.491
I think it's a perfect time because you see what we value.

03:14.972 --> 03:16.034
You see what we're committed to.

03:16.294 --> 03:19.920
You see where God is leading us and what you might be a part of as we move forward.

03:19.940 --> 03:23.125
And so with that, you've been given a little card when you came in.

03:23.145 --> 03:25.409
We're going to talk about that here in a little bit.

03:25.449 --> 03:28.975
But for now, I want to kind of set up where we're heading here this morning.

03:29.476 --> 03:33.582
We celebrate next month, 24 years as a church, which is pretty exciting for us.

03:34.003 --> 03:35.686
And in that, yeah, thank you.

03:36.928 --> 03:38.290
To consider the

03:38.466 --> 03:49.123
beginnings of our church from a core group of college students really wanting to be a part of a movement that taught and exposited the scripture and lived in community and all the things we've been about now for over two decades.

03:49.724 --> 03:54.211
We started the church to help people connect to God and to each other in every neighborhood.

03:54.371 --> 03:55.954
And what we meant by that was

03:56.066 --> 03:58.911
Primarily, we want to be responsible for proclaiming the gospel.

03:58.951 --> 04:03.778
We want people to hear about Jesus Christ, to be reconciled to God through Christ by His Spirit.

04:04.039 --> 04:05.200
We want to teach the Bible.

04:05.521 --> 04:08.165
We want to train, equip, disciple as best we could.

04:08.606 --> 04:11.070
And we've been about that now, as I mentioned, for over two decades.

04:11.110 --> 04:13.413
But we also wanted to help people connect to each other.

04:13.934 --> 04:16.939
We said, let's invite people in to the mess of life together.

04:17.360 --> 04:20.585
Let's walk out this messy process of life with God in community.

04:20.945 --> 04:23.890
Let's acknowledge that community is a bit of a rock tumbler.

04:24.002 --> 04:27.926
that sometimes there's some collisions, sometimes there's some hard conversations.

04:27.966 --> 04:30.549
And in many ways, the best part of the church is the people.

04:31.030 --> 04:34.053
And in some ways, the hardest part of the church is the people.

04:34.874 --> 04:39.479
And yet when we get invited into relationship together, that's where spiritual formation happens.

04:39.599 --> 04:43.623
Transformation happens because we enter into relationships together.

04:43.643 --> 04:45.385
And we said, let's do that in every neighborhood.

04:45.826 --> 04:49.970
And what we meant by that was, let's not just gather crowds and entertain Christians.

04:50.306 --> 04:54.533
Let's train and equip one another to go be the church out in every neighborhood.

04:54.553 --> 04:57.098
Let's go engage the pillars of need in our city.

04:57.138 --> 05:00.925
Let's put the gospel on display in our community.

05:00.945 --> 05:07.035
Let's let our light shine before men and women in such a way that they would see our good works and glorify our Father who is in heaven.

05:07.055 --> 05:11.002
And that's what we've been about now for 20, almost 24 years now.

05:11.143 --> 05:15.410
And in that we've always focused on health and wanted to allow for growth.

05:15.842 --> 05:27.096
When you talk to folks that are in the business world, it's common for people to talk about growth engines and new markets and things that they're doing to better position themselves to a certain demographic.

05:27.136 --> 05:31.241
And that's just never been what we've been about here because the church is not a business.

05:32.062 --> 05:33.964
And thankfully, it's an organic thing.

05:34.004 --> 05:36.468
It grows if it's healthy.

05:37.128 --> 05:39.411
And sometimes it grows more than other times.

05:39.491 --> 05:42.996
But the reality is, is healthy things organically tend to grow.

05:43.016 --> 05:44.978
And so we've been trying to build the trellis.

05:45.218 --> 05:48.123
as this thing's been growing, just to see, Lord, what do you want to do?

05:48.163 --> 05:54.415
We know that you are the lead pastor, we know you're the chief shepherd, and so we're simply trying to respond to you.

05:54.455 --> 06:09.202
And in fact, Paul makes a statement that he watered, or he planted rather, a Paulos watered, but actually it was God who was causing the growth, which means one of the unique things about a church is unless the Lord build the house, the people labor in vain who build it.

06:09.538 --> 06:12.884
unless the Lord watches over the city, the watchman stays awake in vain.

06:13.245 --> 06:21.280
It's a vain thing for us to stay up later to rise early or to eat the bread of painful labor, for he gives to his beloved even while they sleep.

06:21.300 --> 06:25.668
One of the unique things about a church is because it's his, he does whatever he wants with it.

06:25.688 --> 06:26.930
And if it grows, we steward it.

06:27.371 --> 06:29.154
And if it shrinks, we steward it.

06:29.775 --> 06:31.218
And that being said, this last

06:31.330 --> 06:34.073
Several years have been very interesting here at The Well.

06:34.133 --> 06:39.938
And in fact, it's a bit of an inflection point because I can't quite explain what is happening.

06:40.198 --> 06:41.920
And I've seen a lot through the years.

06:42.240 --> 06:48.406
We've grown up together, video shot with really tight jeans and a field somewhere to where we are today.

06:48.446 --> 06:55.693
And we've kind of grown up as a church and seen several movements throughout the decades we've been together.

06:55.713 --> 06:59.256
And that being said, we have doubled in the last 18 months.

06:59.296 --> 07:01.298
And I'm not quite sure I can tell you why.

07:01.762 --> 07:05.548
We've in our kids ministry has grown by 170 percent.

07:06.430 --> 07:09.314
Our student ministry by 150 percent.

07:09.955 --> 07:13.481
And numbers don't tell the whole story, but they do give you a bit of an indication.

07:13.722 --> 07:24.279
In the last six months here at this church, there's been an average of adult and kid attendance of over 8,000 people every single week.

07:24.299 --> 07:26.162
Now, bigger is not better.

07:26.274 --> 07:30.079
And truthfully, all that means then is we have more that we need to steward.

07:30.519 --> 07:36.126
But with that, if you come to one gathering, you might lose sight of what's happening all over in our church.

07:36.206 --> 07:40.812
And so we do 13 different gathering options every week.

07:40.832 --> 07:43.715
And so to see what God is doing, it's just very special.

07:44.196 --> 07:46.018
And so in that, we feel the need to steward it.

07:46.058 --> 07:49.883
And so we started making some plans because it's really not rocket science.

07:49.903 --> 07:55.570
There are five limiting factors of a church that when you hit capacity in any one of these five,

07:55.778 --> 07:56.819
You need to make a change.

07:56.859 --> 07:58.240
You need to find a way to grow.

07:58.821 --> 07:59.922
One obviously is parking.

08:00.703 --> 08:02.745
One is auditorium or sanctuary space.

08:03.285 --> 08:04.747
One is kids space.

08:05.467 --> 08:06.869
One is student space.

08:07.049 --> 08:11.133
And the other, which is a sneaky one for us, is adult classroom space.

08:11.713 --> 08:17.699
And much like when your toddler outgrows their shoes, which is like every other day, then you just have to get new shoes.

08:17.719 --> 08:20.142
You just need to accommodate for that growth.

08:20.202 --> 08:24.626
And so as we continue to process what God is doing, we've hit some of those

08:24.706 --> 08:25.487
Limiting factors.

08:25.527 --> 08:28.950
And so we started to plan like good leaders should.

08:28.970 --> 08:33.976
And we started to come up with some next steps and things that we felt like probably made sense.

08:34.056 --> 08:38.280
Obviously our fig garden campus is beautiful and in need of some renovation there.

08:38.300 --> 08:40.462
And so we thought, okay, let's keep renovating that.

08:40.502 --> 08:42.404
We've got a large campus here.

08:42.464 --> 08:51.794
And so let's continue to grow maybe in this campus and we'll just make some room and it all kind of made sense in terms of where we were heading until it didn't.

08:52.322 --> 08:55.226
And what's interesting about that is we invited our church to pray.

08:55.266 --> 09:01.253
Many of you participated in that over the last three, four, five months and just said, okay, Lord, we don't want to get out in front of you.

09:01.273 --> 09:07.481
I mean, the Bible reminds us that many of the plans of a man's heart, but the counsel of the Lord is what will stand.

09:08.322 --> 09:11.166
That if we commit our plans to the Lord, they'll be established.

09:11.186 --> 09:13.869
And so we said, okay, Lord, this is what we're planning.

09:14.270 --> 09:15.551
Is this what you want?

09:16.152 --> 09:17.714
It makes sense to us.

09:18.274 --> 09:25.862
And we were moving down that road, and as we prayed about it, felt very clearly that the Lord wanted us to go another direction.

09:26.503 --> 09:29.086
Now thankfully, that's not biblically unprecedented.

09:29.526 --> 09:38.175
So if you've read through the book of Acts in Acts chapter 13, the apostle Paul goes with Barnabas on the first missionary journey in Asia Minor, known as modern day Turkey.

09:38.916 --> 09:41.879
They plant churches that may sound familiar to those of you familiar with your Bible.

09:41.899 --> 09:43.101
They plant the church of Galatia.

09:43.141 --> 09:44.402
He writes a book to them.

09:44.578 --> 09:49.145
They plant the church of Colossae, Laodicea, Hierapolis, and Ephesus.

09:49.786 --> 09:53.190
And the ministry there in Asia Minor is actually really, really fruitful.

09:54.072 --> 09:57.597
Timothy comes to faith at that time, like there's really neat things that are happening there.

09:58.118 --> 10:04.547
So in Acts chapter 15, they go back out on a second missionary journey, and it just made sense to go back there.

10:05.108 --> 10:06.770
Like that's where all of the sort of

10:07.074 --> 10:10.318
the dots were kind of aligning them to continue in that journey.

10:10.338 --> 10:12.381
And so go do what you thought you needed to do.

10:12.421 --> 10:13.703
And so they go back.

10:13.763 --> 10:18.249
And in chapter 16, verse five, it says, all the churches there in Asia Minor are strengthened.

10:19.230 --> 10:21.112
And then something very unique happens.

10:22.174 --> 10:25.999
In verse six of Acts 16, they pass through some of the regions there.

10:26.460 --> 10:34.450
They pass through the Phrygian and Galatian region, but they're forbidden by the Holy Spirit to speak the word any longer in Asia.

10:34.978 --> 10:43.529
And then it says in verse seven, they come to a region called Missia, and they were trying to go into Bethynia, but the spirit of Jesus did not permit them.

10:43.589 --> 10:45.731
Now there's a number of places in the Bible.

10:46.012 --> 10:48.114
I just wanna go, okay, wait a minute, what do you mean by that?

10:48.835 --> 10:51.719
Like what did that look like?

10:51.739 --> 10:53.421
For the spirit of God to say no.

10:53.902 --> 10:57.146
For the spirit of Jesus, himself to say no.

10:57.646 --> 11:01.651
And they just keep getting moved geographically more and more westward.

11:01.731 --> 11:02.993
What was that about?

11:03.133 --> 11:03.954
How did that,

11:04.066 --> 11:14.160
And then we know why actually in verse nine, Paul gets a vision of a man on the other side of the Aegean Sea in the region of Macedonia.

11:14.780 --> 11:18.245
And this man in this vision says, come over here and help us.

11:18.966 --> 11:23.532
And when Paul in verse 10 had this vision, it says, immediately he sought to go to Macedonia.

11:24.133 --> 11:31.323
And one of the things I appreciate about the Apostle Paul is he had plans that were established, but when the Lord said, no, I want you to do this.

11:31.343 --> 11:32.384
He said, okay.

11:32.404 --> 11:33.746
And he just shifts gears.

11:34.018 --> 11:38.423
He just immediately goes and he's just obedient to whatever God had for him.

11:38.443 --> 11:52.941
And if you recall what happens next in the book of Acts, he goes over to Macedonia, plants of church in Philippi, Thessalonica, Berea, Athens, Corinth, that entire region has changed because he immediately went where God called him to go.

11:53.602 --> 12:03.474
And I share that because as we've been sort of praying about what was next, everything in our plans said here at this campus, sanctuary, sanctuary, sanctuary.

12:03.938 --> 12:05.100
Let's build a sanctuary.

12:05.600 --> 12:06.582
Let's make more room.

12:06.702 --> 12:07.683
Let's make more parking.

12:07.723 --> 12:11.428
Let's repurpose the current auditorium for more kid space.

12:11.729 --> 12:15.735
Let's check a number of those limiting factor boxes at our fig garden campus.

12:15.775 --> 12:18.699
Let's renovate that like that all made sense.

12:18.959 --> 12:22.464
And as we prayed our elders and it was, I can't explain it.

12:23.345 --> 12:28.813
We didn't get a vision of a Macedonian man by any means, but there was just such a sense of unity together.

12:28.833 --> 12:32.498
I don't think that's what God has for us now.

12:32.834 --> 12:37.800
That may be an eventual step, but I think there's some things that we need to do before that.

12:38.441 --> 12:40.263
And so we're gonna make a pivot.

12:40.844 --> 12:45.109
And much like Paul immediately pivoted, we're gonna share with you what that pivot looks like.

12:45.169 --> 12:47.232
Now the good news is it's not a complete departure.

12:47.832 --> 12:49.494
We're still committed to the next generation.

12:49.554 --> 12:50.776
It's still about Psalm 71.

12:50.896 --> 13:01.369
Oh God, you have taught us from our youth and we still declare your wondrous deeds that even when we are old and gray, oh God, do not forsake us until we declare your strength to this generation, your power, to all who are to come.

13:01.389 --> 13:02.290
It's still about

13:02.402 --> 13:03.283
the next generation.

13:03.603 --> 13:06.827
It's also for us about teaching, training, equipping, and discipling.

13:06.868 --> 13:07.989
So that's not changing.

13:08.029 --> 13:10.011
We want to strengthen this generation.

13:10.412 --> 13:11.513
We want to reach the next.

13:11.593 --> 13:16.740
We know that we need both the more seasoned vintage and the passionate youth.

13:17.160 --> 13:18.422
That's the life of a church.

13:18.442 --> 13:20.264
And so we recognize that.

13:20.925 --> 13:23.468
But what we do know is we need to take some next steps.

13:23.508 --> 13:28.274
And so we're going to be launching here today another campaign called Cultivate.

13:28.930 --> 13:40.304
And just to give you a little bit of history on that, one of the things we did early on when we launched Cultivate back in 2018 with the tight jeans in the field is we said, hey, first thing we want to do is something different.

13:40.745 --> 13:49.957
Instead of doing a capital campaign where you put a thermometer on the wall, you do drive by guiltings every week, everybody feels completely shamed into giving.

13:50.497 --> 13:51.519
What if we did it different?

13:51.579 --> 13:53.701
And in fact, what if we reframe the whole thing?

13:54.342 --> 13:57.426
And so let's invite people to participate as they feel led

13:57.602 --> 14:01.787
And the first half a million dollars that comes in, let's give that away.

14:01.807 --> 14:02.948
People said, that makes no sense.

14:02.968 --> 14:04.851
Why would you do a capital campaign and give money away?

14:04.871 --> 14:09.716
I said, well, if we have a value of generosity, I think that actually reinforces that value.

14:09.736 --> 14:11.959
And so let's actually reflect that.

14:12.059 --> 14:15.383
And so we picked 11 organizations in 2018.

14:15.543 --> 14:18.547
These are all gospel centered initiatives in our city.

14:18.567 --> 14:24.754
And they were, interestingly enough, combating human trafficking, helping with orphan care,

14:24.866 --> 14:31.835
and dealing with or addressing the needs of at-risk youth, which is interesting because you'll see there's a bit of a golden thread there.

14:32.376 --> 14:37.183
In 2021, we did another round of Cultivate and we said, look, first fruits was awesome.

14:37.203 --> 14:38.024
Let's do that again.

14:38.064 --> 14:46.976
But instead of 11 organizations, let's pick one because at that time, the Fresno Mission, which is doing amazing work continuing here in our city.

14:46.996 --> 14:48.838
They've been doing it for a generation now.

14:49.419 --> 14:54.706
They have just purchased the Sierra Hospital, which is on Dakota and between Blackstone and

14:54.978 --> 14:58.742
the freeway, and they converted it to a place called City Center.

14:59.543 --> 15:01.946
And so they've got this ministry and city center.

15:01.986 --> 15:05.790
They're bringing the best of our city by way of nonprofits into city center.

15:06.250 --> 15:11.055
But one of the things, as we discussed it with them, that we all felt was lacking, was a church there.

15:11.796 --> 15:15.480
I said, well, what if we planted a church at city center called City Church?

15:15.620 --> 15:18.944
We had a pastor who was on our staff, Mark Sneaker, I call him Snezer.

15:18.964 --> 15:24.530
I go, hey, Snezer, what if we launch you over to City Church and plant this thing?

15:24.802 --> 15:26.164
And he said, man, that sounds awesome.

15:26.184 --> 15:29.750
So we took a half a million dollars and we planted a church called City Church.

15:29.770 --> 15:31.853
Now the other day I was at an event for the mission.

15:32.674 --> 15:38.103
And they were showing pictures of some of the ministry that's happening there at City Center and at City Church.

15:38.123 --> 15:39.425
And it was so encouraging.

15:39.725 --> 15:42.770
Because as I'm looking at these pictures of the events that are happening,

15:42.978 --> 15:47.722
They're ministering to some of the most vulnerable in our city, but I'm like, hey, that face looks familiar.

15:47.762 --> 15:49.404
That person leads a life group for us.

15:49.784 --> 15:51.565
That person has been around our church forever.

15:51.886 --> 15:53.387
That person works in our kids' ministry.

15:53.407 --> 15:54.888
That person works with our student ministry.

15:55.389 --> 16:04.977
All of these people that are serving at City Church had been engaged and are engaged here as part of our family, worshiping here, and then ministering there in City Church.

16:04.997 --> 16:08.921
I'm like, look at the body, be in the body in every neighborhood.

16:08.961 --> 16:11.603
And so we're still a part of what's happening there.

16:11.623 --> 16:12.964
But I wanna tell you what we're gonna do this

16:12.944 --> 16:13.184
time.

16:14.025 --> 16:21.274
We're going to launch a campaign, as I mentioned, and we are going to do first fruits, but we don't think that half a million dollars is enough.

16:21.294 --> 16:28.943
We want to give away a million dollars and strategically reinvest a million dollars into three now local initiatives.

16:28.963 --> 16:30.645
And I want to tell you about those.

16:30.665 --> 16:33.328
The first that we're going to partner with is called the Care Portal.

16:34.169 --> 16:35.871
And the Care Portal is fascinating.

16:36.351 --> 16:42.258
It's a web-based care share platform designed to connect people of need

16:42.498 --> 16:44.921
with people of means in the community.

16:44.942 --> 16:45.743
I'll give you an example.

16:46.644 --> 16:53.694
Let's say in Southwest Fresno, there's a family that is bringing in at-risk youth, and they're bringing in orphaned children.

16:54.115 --> 16:56.238
And let's say one of those children is on the floor.

16:56.278 --> 16:57.780
They don't have a bed for that child.

16:58.321 --> 17:10.258
Well, if social worker hears about that, social worker's gonna say, hey, look, to keep the kid, you've gotta have a bed for that child to sleep in, or we're gonna have to replace or re-put the child to a different home, okay?

17:10.402 --> 17:15.767
Just out of curiosity, if I said to you right now, we've got a situation in Southwest Fresno, there's a child that needs a bed.

17:15.807 --> 17:18.390
How many of you have a bed that you could help provide for that child?

17:18.410 --> 17:20.632
Raise your hand if you've got a bed you might be able to provide.

17:21.172 --> 17:24.976
What if I said to you, hey, it's $200 to get a bed for that child?

17:25.256 --> 17:28.479
How many of you could get your neighbors or your life group or your family together?

17:28.720 --> 17:32.263
You could all pitch in and you could come up with 200 bucks to get that kid into bed?

17:32.283 --> 17:32.783
Okay, question.

17:33.144 --> 17:34.065
Why haven't you done that?

17:36.247 --> 17:38.629
You haven't done that because you didn't know there was a need.

17:38.909 --> 17:39.730
What if you did?

17:40.450 --> 17:43.353
And so what care portal does is makes the needs available.

17:43.794 --> 17:46.557
So as your life group gets together and says, hey, man, we should do something.

17:46.977 --> 17:50.461
I mean, James says pure and undefiled religion is caring for widows and orphans.

17:50.541 --> 17:54.906
Let's find a situation where we can go help and we can help meet that need.

17:54.946 --> 17:58.650
Now the person with the need is matched with the people of means.

17:58.950 --> 18:02.414
And now that kid stays in a functional home because you help provide a bed.

18:02.434 --> 18:03.895
Isn't that awesome?

18:03.915 --> 18:06.258
In Acts chapter two and in Acts chapter four,

18:06.498 --> 18:12.126
The early church, as it grew, it says that there was no needy person among them.

18:12.347 --> 18:14.069
Now I find that hard to believe.

18:14.970 --> 18:19.497
Do you mean to tell me that there was actually no needy person among them?

18:20.318 --> 18:31.154
Or were the needy people that were among them who had the needs known by people who had the means so the people of means simply met the need and therefore there was no needy person among them?

18:31.174 --> 18:33.778
That feels to me like what the church is called to be.

18:33.954 --> 18:34.815
It gets even better.

18:35.136 --> 18:42.286
Let's say that family in Southwest Fresno is across the street from image church by way of example.

18:42.706 --> 18:44.669
Well, image church is pastored by Jay Spence.

18:45.230 --> 18:47.013
Jay Spence has been connected to our church.

18:47.033 --> 18:48.094
He's a lead pastor there.

18:48.154 --> 18:51.559
We love Jay Spence and he's killing it in Southwest Fresno.

18:51.579 --> 18:56.466
What if we said, hey, Jay Spence, there's a need that's been posted across the street from your church?

18:56.930 --> 19:03.581
But chances are, if that family wants to come to church, they're not gonna come here, they're probably gonna go across the street to you.

19:03.961 --> 19:10.251
So we're gonna meet the need, but we want your church to provide the need to that family so the need gets met.

19:10.532 --> 19:17.042
We'll be the supply line, you be the front line, so if and when that family wants to come to church, they walk across the street to your place.

19:17.082 --> 19:19.506
Now the kingdom is being exalted.

19:19.554 --> 19:20.455
not our castle.

19:20.756 --> 19:22.859
That sounds absolutely fantastic.

19:22.919 --> 19:25.742
And so we're gonna partner with the care portal.

19:25.763 --> 19:28.126
We'll be telling you more about that in the coming weeks.

19:28.146 --> 19:30.309
There's two other initiatives though that we want you to know about.

19:31.050 --> 19:35.876
One is called Our Valley Cares, and the other is called The Spee's House.

19:35.977 --> 19:42.706
And so I met with Matt Dildine, who's the CEO of The Mission, and I said, okay, tell me, Matt, about what you're doing.

19:42.726 --> 19:43.747
I mean, I care about this.

19:44.428 --> 19:45.429
You're a part of our church.

19:45.490 --> 19:48.754
The mission is obviously something we're heavily invested in.

19:48.994 --> 19:50.296
Tell me about these two initiatives.

19:50.376 --> 19:53.079
I wanna make sure when I communicate it, I've got the heart.

19:53.259 --> 19:55.081
And as I was listening to him, I said, you know what?

19:55.842 --> 19:59.887
On second thought, why don't you just join us and you share the heart because you're living in it.

19:59.907 --> 20:03.291
And so why don't you welcome CEO of The Mission, Matt Dilduy.

20:09.058 --> 20:09.959
Thank you, buddy, for coming.

20:10.059 --> 20:15.506
So tell us a little bit, as we hung out the other day, I was like, okay, we need to hear from you on this.

20:15.714 --> 20:25.603
Tell us about these initiatives of our valley cares and the space house, how are they connected and connect the dots for us to that golden thread of at risk youth.

20:25.723 --> 20:28.406
Yeah, so thank you so much for being here.

20:28.566 --> 20:31.329
This is my home church for those you don't know, been here for 15 years.

20:31.989 --> 20:37.094
And you know, I've loved during that time that we have had such a focus as a church about trying to reach the next generation.

20:37.975 --> 20:45.362
And I love that because I am in my work every day and we see such evil and I leave work all the time thinking

20:45.506 --> 20:47.449
We just flat out need more Christians.

20:47.629 --> 20:50.574
We just flat out do because evil is such a real thing.

20:51.435 --> 21:01.370
But the evil that we see when you're dealing with trafficking or homeless, when we start looking at these issues, we see that so much of that starts when they're young.

21:01.390 --> 21:10.724
90% of human trafficking adult victims have actually experienced from the child welfare system.

21:10.744 --> 21:11.826
You're actually

21:11.906 --> 21:19.674
a youth aging out of the foster care system is more likely to become homeless than an adult exiting prison.

21:20.455 --> 21:28.023
If you go and survey the average person who's lived on the street for an excess of one year and asked, when is the first time in their life the experienced homelessness?

21:28.323 --> 21:31.346
40% will tell you from zero to 14.

21:32.107 --> 21:38.834
And just flat out what we see is that the highest population, the highest population, the population

21:39.042 --> 21:44.610
Fresno, California, United States is increasing the fastest is homeless kids.

21:44.850 --> 21:47.013
That's the number one population is increasing.

21:48.195 --> 21:55.505
And so we see all this and we're seeing these kids coming to us and they're coming up to us at the mall and even this last two services, right?

21:55.866 --> 21:57.068
Both services, right?

21:57.108 --> 22:04.458
And Thursday and Thursday in this morning, I had two different people come up to me and say, hey, we have this, I'm a school counselor, I have an 18 year old, she has no place else to go.

22:05.139 --> 22:07.282
She's getting kicked out, no place else to go.

22:07.458 --> 22:09.200
What we're seeing is this explosion.

22:10.081 --> 22:15.307
And so we said, man, what if we put a stake in the ground, said not in our community?

22:15.868 --> 22:34.130
What if we created a system of care that's gonna bring together all the partners and say, we're gonna create the best system of care in the entire country to make sure that no youth who's in crisis, every youth who's in crisis has a place to go and the absolute best system of care waiting there for them.

22:34.274 --> 22:35.436
rooted in the gospel.

22:35.496 --> 22:36.897
What if we could do that?

22:36.917 --> 22:38.519
And that's when we came up with our Valley Cares.

22:39.341 --> 22:44.047
The Our Valley Cares initiative, though, is more than just a one organization initiative.

22:44.728 --> 22:51.697
You know, I kind of like, you know, you know, read in the New Testament, Paul, and he's praying for all these churches around, right?

22:52.017 --> 22:52.237
Right?

22:52.618 --> 22:56.503
And I think about all the ministries in our community that need help.

22:56.583 --> 23:02.130
And so part of our Valley Cares, we really created this fundraising platform, this funding platform,

23:02.306 --> 23:06.510
to help bring together these organizations and then be able to help raise money for them.

23:06.530 --> 23:11.634
Now, why would one nonprofit ministry raise money for another nonprofit ministry?

23:11.654 --> 23:17.779
It's kind of like when a church who's raising money for its buildings gives money to another organization.

23:17.839 --> 23:23.184
It's kind of like we have this great big God who's a God of abundance and not a God of scarcity.

23:23.204 --> 23:24.665
You can say it's all his resources.

23:25.066 --> 23:27.128
And when we lean into that, we receive his favor.

23:27.148 --> 23:32.292
And so what we're doing is the R Valley Cares Initiative is we're taking money to be able to distribute

23:32.272 --> 23:34.034
and to build, help bring up a system.

23:34.695 --> 23:38.821
But as far as that system, we needed to bring, to also build the very best place.

23:39.642 --> 23:54.823
You know, we deal with kids who've been trafficked, who've been 12 different foster homes, who were not born with the best of parents, not born with the best, you know, weren't born with the college, the college bank accounts, were born well beyond where the starting line should be in their lives.

23:55.484 --> 23:56.746
They never get the best of anything.

23:57.948 --> 23:59.570
But I also noticed that the single

23:59.682 --> 24:16.361
best thing, when you have had years or decades of abuse, abandonment, trauma, neglect, the very best thing we have to fight, those years of abuse is years of being part of a faith community that loves you and cares for you, that you're in the gospel.

24:16.962 --> 24:19.265
But that has to be able to occur in some place.

24:20.066 --> 24:23.349
So as part of that, we want to build a speech house.

24:23.369 --> 24:27.314
We want to build the very best ministry and crisis center for youth.

24:27.522 --> 24:29.725
not just locally in the entire country.

24:29.945 --> 24:37.754
I am so glad that I get to pick up my kids here on Tuesday and Wednesday nights, and it looks like an anthill full of kids that are reaching the gospel, receiving the gospel.

24:38.695 --> 24:40.778
And I'm so happy for these projects.

24:41.679 --> 24:49.709
But I know the kids that are staying on my campus, the kids who are wandering at fashion for at night, the kids are being trafficked, they need the best place to go to.

24:50.410 --> 24:52.732
And that's why we're building the space house.

24:52.752 --> 24:54.094
My kids need something different.

24:54.334 --> 24:56.797
The kids that we work with, they're number one request.

24:56.817 --> 24:57.458
You know what that is?

24:57.634 --> 24:58.355
a wash machine.

24:59.137 --> 25:01.020
Never think of a youth room with a wash machine, right?

25:01.380 --> 25:03.444
That's the number one request.

25:03.464 --> 25:05.247
So we want to build this place called the Spies House.

25:05.307 --> 25:13.060
It will be this ministry central to provide housing, job placement, a place for them to go, food, a store, a place for them to nap, a place for them to wash their clothes.

25:13.401 --> 25:23.378
But more importantly, it's a place where they can go 24 hours a day to receive the community that they have not received up to that point in life, rooted in the gospel.

25:23.490 --> 25:28.256
Matt was sharing a story about kids that'll hang out in the parking lot, fashion, fair mall all night.

25:28.316 --> 25:30.219
He said, why do they hang out in the parking lot?

25:30.239 --> 25:35.867
It's not necessarily to participate in nonsense, so they won't be victimized, so they stay up all night.

25:36.347 --> 25:40.593
Then they come over to City Center to find a couch where they can get some sleep.

25:40.993 --> 25:42.796
So we're gonna provide that safe place for them.

25:42.836 --> 25:46.721
The name Speeds, by the way, comes from H. Speeds, who's now with Jesus.

25:47.282 --> 25:50.386
H and Randy White were kind of the OG,

25:50.498 --> 25:56.706
relocators in our city, they were going in to do asset-based community development before anybody else was thinking about that.

25:56.746 --> 25:58.428
And literally, I think they wrote the book on it.

25:59.049 --> 26:02.733
And so they both sort of pioneered community transformation.

26:02.753 --> 26:10.343
And so in honor of age and in keeping with his vision of being a safe place for youth, that's the Our Valley Cares and the Spee's House.

26:10.383 --> 26:11.364
So appreciate it, buddy.

26:11.384 --> 26:11.704
Thank you.

26:12.245 --> 26:13.106
All right.

26:17.122 --> 26:22.691
If you're interested in more information, all three of those organizations are in our courtyard at both campuses right now.

26:22.751 --> 26:25.495
You can go get some more details and learn more about that.

26:25.916 --> 26:28.520
Let me tell you a little bit about what we're going to do with our fig garden campus.

26:28.580 --> 26:31.584
So if you've been with us, you know, we did the kids' buildings first.

26:31.664 --> 26:33.067
We did the sanctuary second.

26:33.107 --> 26:36.151
We're now going to do the fellowship hall for a number of reasons.

26:36.251 --> 26:39.136
One, nobody in 2026 knows what a fellowship hall is.

26:39.617 --> 26:42.020
And we've learned a little bit from doing a student center here.

26:42.341 --> 26:45.746
We're going to convert that from a fellowship hall to a student center

26:45.826 --> 26:48.050
full audio-visual lighting upgrade.

26:48.651 --> 26:53.338
We're going to expand it out a little bit to match the storefront glass that's already on that campus.

26:53.719 --> 26:58.767
Perhaps even remodel the kitchen, new play structure, perhaps a block wall along the canal.

26:59.489 --> 27:05.458
We're looking to upgrade and finish that fourth and final building on that campus to upgrade it.

27:05.498 --> 27:07.261
That is part of this process.

27:07.281 --> 27:12.530
And then regarding here at this campus, we're going to take the current pantry and office

27:12.610 --> 27:16.537
pole barn and cold storage located on the northern part of our property.

27:16.557 --> 27:19.884
We're going to demo that and build what we're calling a ministry center.

27:20.364 --> 27:26.636
And a ministry center is a centralized office in complex, but also an adult training center.

27:26.656 --> 27:35.052
It's going to have classroom space in it, perhaps even a fourth and fifth grade room to make some room out of our kids building to temporarily house them there.

27:35.072 --> 27:36.274
I say temporarily.

27:36.354 --> 27:49.326
in that once we do the eventual move, if that's what the Lord has for us and build a sanctuary, then we'll repurpose this auditorium for kids and our fourth and fifth graders will come here, but it'll be an intermediate step to make a little bit of room for them.

27:49.366 --> 27:52.594
It'll be a one, maybe two story.

27:52.706 --> 27:53.848
office complex.

27:53.868 --> 27:59.316
We're not quite sure what it's going to look like yet, which is why we have nothing to show you yet, but we're heading down that road.

27:59.717 --> 28:11.475
The other thing that'll do for us is that means the million dollars of portables that we've put on the property, we can vacate those by way of officeing and convert those now to some adult breakout space rooms as well.

28:11.535 --> 28:13.778
So we think that's a good next step.

28:14.018 --> 28:15.540
for us as we move forward.

28:15.560 --> 28:18.745
Let's talk just for a little bit about the financing of all of this.

28:19.206 --> 28:27.678
In 2018, when we took the first step of Cultivate, we ended up taking on a very large debt load of 17 million in debt.

28:27.698 --> 28:30.423
And I have said that number now for eight years, a lot.

28:30.943 --> 28:32.806
And there's still a lot of zeros that are there.

28:33.788 --> 28:38.334
But thankfully, that's not a debt load that is hindering our ministries at all.

28:38.775 --> 28:40.818
We can service that.

28:41.058 --> 28:42.801
without having to impact anything.

28:43.201 --> 28:46.707
And in fact, as of today, it's down to 16.3 million.

28:47.047 --> 28:51.795
And so we understand the concern of being over your skis, if you will, with debt.

28:51.815 --> 28:55.300
And thankfully, that is not something that's hindering us at this point.

28:55.361 --> 29:04.254
But when we took on now this new student center build and renovated the sanctuary over at our fig garden campus, we took on an additional $3 million in debt.

29:04.815 --> 29:07.840
And the goal was to pay that down as soon as possible.

29:07.860 --> 29:09.042
Well, in September,

29:09.122 --> 29:11.645
That was paid down to about 1.7 million.

29:12.546 --> 29:18.593
And I'm happy to tell you that as of today, the current debt that we are still carrying from the Student Center is zero.

29:18.974 --> 29:21.537
So we have paid that off, which is wonderful.

29:23.279 --> 29:28.666
Which means then we can step into this next Cultivate effort without carrying any additional debt.

29:28.686 --> 29:33.832
We're just currently still servicing that 16.3 million as we move forward.

29:33.852 --> 29:39.058
That being said, we really would like this campaign, if possible, to be primarily a cash

29:39.170 --> 29:44.158
build, which means we'd like to not take on any additional debt if we could avoid it.

29:44.218 --> 29:48.404
Now, that being said, thankfully, this is a very generous church and giving is up.

29:48.425 --> 29:57.038
So we do have some headroom if we needed to take on some additional, but we're very careful to not get too far into debt service so it hinders ministry.

29:57.058 --> 30:04.289
So the number for this capital campaign, this round of cultivate is a $20 million number.

30:04.390 --> 30:04.690
Now,

30:04.898 --> 30:06.220
That's a lot of money as well.

30:06.260 --> 30:10.827
But if you've tried to build anything in this environment currently, everything's expensive.

30:11.388 --> 30:14.553
So we recognize it's a lot, but here's what we did in the meantime.

30:15.193 --> 30:19.300
We decided, hey, look, we need to reach out to our leaders and see if our leaders would go first.

30:19.380 --> 30:20.942
And so we reached out to some leaders.

30:21.383 --> 30:34.162
We did a small event a couple of weeks ago and invited our leaders to go first so that when we went public with the campaign, we can have some monies already committed to it and make that $20 million number a little bit more manageable.

30:34.690 --> 30:49.069
It was approximately 350 commitments that came in from our leaders and they committed not one million, not two million, not three million, not four million, but five million dollars.

30:49.850 --> 30:55.077
Which means the current cultivate need additionally is not 20 million.

30:55.157 --> 30:56.739
We're already a quarter of the way there.

30:56.779 --> 31:01.125
It's 15 million dollars and we haven't even gone public yet to our congregations.

31:01.165 --> 31:04.690
And so the generosity of our leaders to lead well

31:04.802 --> 31:07.947
is before us, and so we're very thankful for that.

31:08.408 --> 31:11.794
And so with that, though, I want to walk us through if we can this card.

31:12.815 --> 31:24.454
If you came here today and you said, what's Cultivate, we've got some information on this side of the card that you might want to take a look at to get up to speed on what we're trying to accomplish, but I want to focus on this part if we can in the time that's remaining.

31:25.516 --> 31:31.506
Obviously, general name and info if you're comfortable participating in Cultivate, and I would hope

31:31.586 --> 31:41.820
Based on the first box that you see there, I would love for everybody to be willing to participate, at least by checking that first box and saying, hey, look, I may not be able to give anything, but I can most certainly pray.

31:42.261 --> 31:43.723
That's not the least you can do.

31:44.043 --> 31:46.026
That's actually the greatest thing you can do.

31:46.346 --> 31:49.691
And so if you'd be comfortable saying, hey, I'm gonna commit to pray for Cultivate.

31:49.831 --> 31:51.333
Let's see what the Lord has for us.

31:51.714 --> 31:55.219
Check that first box there and commit to pray for Cultivate would be great.

31:55.259 --> 32:00.626
The second box says, I'm willing to begin to give to the well just in general.

32:01.058 --> 32:03.221
And if that's you, that would be awesome.

32:03.261 --> 32:04.923
Now, why would we put that on this card?

32:04.963 --> 32:19.542
Well, if we have grown and doubled in the last 18 months, then that means there's a lot of you here who've not yet participated in supporting just the general movement of helping people connect to God and to each other in every neighborhood.

32:19.963 --> 32:24.128
And if you would be interested in doing that, that would help tremendously.

32:24.649 --> 32:28.594
Even if you say, hey, I'm new to the church, I'm not willing to commit to cultivate yet, even just that,

32:28.802 --> 32:34.491
would help continue to fund the various ministries that we're a part of and the various initiatives that we're rolling out.

32:34.511 --> 32:36.875
But the third one is what I want to focus on now.

32:37.075 --> 32:39.299
And that's making a cultivate commitment.

32:39.800 --> 32:41.082
It's a three year campaign.

32:41.102 --> 32:45.889
So we just want you to pray about what would you be comfortable doing over three years?

32:45.929 --> 32:50.537
And let me remind you of what we said last week as it relates to both general giving and giving to cultivate.

32:51.118 --> 32:56.306
One of the most important things is to give whatever you feel that you can give with joy.

32:56.962 --> 33:04.007
If the idea of giving to the well or giving to cultivate gives you hives and gives you no joy, then don't give anything.

33:04.589 --> 33:05.713
Bring your Bible next week.

33:05.753 --> 33:07.258
We'll start our series called Monarchy.

33:07.278 --> 33:09.586
We're going to look at King Saul.

33:09.730 --> 33:14.576
David, King Solomon, and King Jesus, and we'll just keep walking this messy process out together.

33:14.976 --> 33:16.759
There is no guilt here at the well.

33:16.779 --> 33:19.102
It's invitation, we're not shoving you in the back.

33:19.442 --> 33:23.567
But we do want to challenge those of you that want to participate to fill out a card.

33:23.687 --> 33:26.991
One of the things I love about our church is we tend to have a bit of a chip on our shoulder.

33:27.612 --> 33:33.580
So with both campaigns that we've done previous people are like, look, I'm gonna give, but I'm not filling out your stupid card.

33:33.720 --> 33:35.602
And in some ways, I kind of respect it.

33:36.290 --> 33:40.578
I kind of respect it because I'm like that too, but let me tell you why we need the card, okay?

33:41.160 --> 33:47.733
Even if you're not sure and you want to aim conservative, totally fine, totally fine, because I think people didn't want to be locked in.

33:48.053 --> 33:52.141
You can adjust your giving commitment anytime you want.

33:52.342 --> 33:53.263
It's yours to adjust.

33:53.624 --> 33:54.706
Here's why that will help us.

33:55.247 --> 33:58.674
If we get commitments in sufficient to the amount that we need,

33:59.266 --> 34:09.537
And we can justify to the bank and substantiate that we're on pace to actually fulfill that, then they can give us a construction loan and we can move forward much quicker otherwise.

34:09.797 --> 34:13.400
We're gonna have to wait till every dime's in the account before we can launch out.

34:13.701 --> 34:17.064
And if you've built anything, it usually takes longer than you would like.

34:17.104 --> 34:19.807
And so that will help us move forward much, much quicker.

34:20.187 --> 34:24.312
And then you can just let us know how you wanna fulfill that, whether it's every month or this or that.

34:24.352 --> 34:26.674
Now here's one of the things we learned early on.

34:26.786 --> 34:29.309
For years, my wife and I gave you a check.

34:29.990 --> 34:33.995
Now, this is old school, so I don't know if you even write checks anymore, but we gave you a check.

34:34.015 --> 34:35.657
And every once in a while, we'd forget, right?

34:35.697 --> 34:37.119
You just life happened, you forget.

34:37.420 --> 34:39.302
Then you're like, okay, well, then I'll double it.

34:39.622 --> 34:43.267
We've ever tried to double something like that, like, ooh, that stings a little bit.

34:43.808 --> 34:44.649
But you know what I realized?

34:44.709 --> 34:46.591
George Brown got paid every single month.

34:47.573 --> 34:49.355
I'm like, I love George, but he doesn't deserve it.

34:49.375 --> 34:50.296
I'm gonna give to the Lord.

34:50.316 --> 34:51.658
That's my financial value.

34:52.419 --> 34:54.962
George got paid every month because he took it out of my account every month.

34:55.426 --> 34:56.748
And so I said, well, can we do that?

34:56.829 --> 35:05.024
So we brought in recurring online giving, which allows you to simply set it and forget it, meaning you don't have to cut the check.

35:05.044 --> 35:07.849
Now some people are like, no, no, no, God wants my check.

35:08.049 --> 35:14.101
Look, if that's the case, we have boxes in the back, you can bring your check in, totally fine or mail it to the office, that's fine.

35:14.421 --> 35:19.090
But for those of you that are tech savvy and want to do something online, if you go to our website,

35:19.362 --> 35:21.745
click on the give page, all of the details are there.

35:22.126 --> 35:26.591
You can even do a Cultivate Envelope digitally on that site if you would like.

35:26.691 --> 35:30.116
Now, as we close four things I wanna just encourage you with, all right?

35:30.136 --> 35:34.782
First is I wanna encourage you, because we have to answer the question, what are we gonna do in the meantime?

35:35.563 --> 35:41.090
Because we still have parking issues at both campuses, we still have some auditory issues, right?

35:41.110 --> 35:42.111
We've got some issues.

35:42.592 --> 35:43.913
And so what do we do in the meantime?

35:44.174 --> 35:47.538
One, I wanna encourage you to migration, meaning,

35:47.714 --> 35:51.219
We do 13 gathering options every single week.

35:51.239 --> 35:56.007
Some indoors, some outdoors, some in Fresno, some in Clovis, some on Thursday, some on Sunday.

35:56.728 --> 36:04.480
If you do not have children and could migrate to midweek, there is plenty of room at midweek for more adults.

36:04.880 --> 36:11.991
There's not more room for kids because we do our reengaged ministry and our merged ministry and oftentimes our children's ministry is full.

36:12.292 --> 36:16.498
But if you don't have kids and you want to come to midweek, it's the best kept secret at the well, come to midweek.

36:16.610 --> 36:17.231
Come join us.

36:17.591 --> 36:24.138
If you're a college or young adult student to move to the PM gathering, our rowdy's hang out at seven, come.

36:24.158 --> 36:26.100
They've been open in the coffee house and hanging out.

36:26.440 --> 36:27.902
I heard karaoke went down the other night.

36:27.922 --> 36:28.803
It was awesome.

36:28.823 --> 36:31.366
So come and hang out in our PM gathering.

36:31.386 --> 36:32.026
That will be great.

36:32.487 --> 36:38.553
If you live in central Fresno, our Figardan campus has a little bit of room, not a ton, but a little bit.

36:38.673 --> 36:39.795
If you want to go check it out.

36:40.135 --> 36:43.058
They mirror the morning gathering times that we do here at Clovis.

36:43.138 --> 36:45.623
over our fig garden campus and we're a multi-site church.

36:45.643 --> 36:48.449
We're one church in multiple locations.

36:48.529 --> 36:53.139
And then if you're open to it, we're looking at putting some shade in our outdoor theater.

36:53.199 --> 36:57.508
If possible, we're exploring what that would look like to make that a more viable option.

36:58.389 --> 37:02.578
Mornings like today might be a nice time to do it, but truthfully,

37:02.658 --> 37:05.521
if the fog is rolling in, maybe not, but we're gonna make that available.

37:05.841 --> 37:10.246
And then in our student center auditorium, we're launching what we're calling a family venue.

37:10.266 --> 37:15.612
They're meeting currently now, but we're gonna be plussing that venue to have kids, kids for your kids.

37:15.672 --> 37:16.974
They can draw it up and whatnot.

37:17.014 --> 37:19.076
So if you wanna be with your kids, go in there.

37:19.096 --> 37:20.217
You're certainly welcome to.

37:20.237 --> 37:22.820
We're trying to create as much space as we can.

37:22.860 --> 37:23.661
So migration.

37:23.741 --> 37:27.025
Second, we wanna encourage you to change up your routine a little bit.

37:27.645 --> 37:31.890
So most folks, you come right when the gathering starts and then try to park

37:32.290 --> 37:35.234
and then try to get your coffee and then try to come and find a seat.

37:35.535 --> 37:40.862
And unfortunately, oftentimes that makes it a little bit difficult because you're just late, not your fault.

37:41.062 --> 37:42.805
It's just the occupational hazard of coming late.

37:43.366 --> 37:51.717
That being said, if you came a little early, easier to find a parking place, you can get your coffee and, I don't know if you've noticed this, you all sit in the same places.

37:52.979 --> 37:56.224
Which means like the same five or 10 people are around you almost every week.

37:56.544 --> 38:00.850
So it also would give you the opportunity to get to know the people that you're sitting around

38:00.962 --> 38:05.089
so that now strangers can become friends and a larger church can feel small.

38:05.129 --> 38:08.234
So would you encourage or encourage you to change your routine?

38:08.294 --> 38:10.698
Third, I would encourage you to get connected.

38:11.519 --> 38:12.120
Get connected.

38:12.320 --> 38:20.053
As we're continuing to grow, the focus over these next three years are teaching, training, equipping, and discipling, but it's going to require you to take a next step.

38:20.794 --> 38:23.378
We can't force you into community.

38:23.714 --> 38:24.795
but we can't invite you.

38:24.955 --> 38:31.843
And I will say this, if you don't take the step into a group or on a team, it will be very easy for you to feel lost here.

38:32.484 --> 38:34.626
And so we wanna encourage you to make that step.

38:35.267 --> 38:36.268
Why get in a group?

38:36.288 --> 38:37.169
Why get on a team?

38:37.209 --> 38:38.991
Because you'll be known and no others.

38:40.153 --> 38:42.255
You'll be cared for and you'll care for others.

38:42.636 --> 38:44.838
You'll be prayed for and you'll be able to pray for others.

38:45.539 --> 38:48.042
And it helps a larger church feel small.

38:48.202 --> 38:51.826
And then finally, I wanna encourage you to participate and cultivate

38:52.418 --> 38:53.940
as you feel led from the Lord.

38:53.960 --> 38:57.083
See, the beauty of this is you get to pray about it, do whatever God puts on your heart to do.

38:57.704 --> 38:59.265
And it's between you and him.

39:00.106 --> 39:17.425
But what I do know is if we will engage, especially those that have never engaged with us before, if we will engage everybody, if a small group of 350 leaders can move the needle like they did, maybe it's possible that we close the rest of it together with whatever widows might God lays on your heart to give.

39:17.485 --> 39:17.665
Amen.

39:18.126 --> 39:22.290
I'm gonna close by just reading Ephesians chapter three, just a good reminder as we close up.

39:22.402 --> 39:25.185
hear this week and head into this cultivate effort.

39:25.265 --> 39:39.739
It says, now to him who was able to do abundantly beyond all that we ask or think according to his power that works within us, to him be the glory in the church and in Christ Jesus to all generations forever and forever.

39:40.319 --> 39:40.740
Amen.

39:41.040 --> 39:41.280
Amen.

39:41.300 --> 39:41.701
Let's pray.

39:42.061 --> 39:43.783
God, would you do exactly that?

39:43.823 --> 39:47.907
Would you do exceedingly abundantly beyond all we can ask or think?

39:47.927 --> 39:50.689
And Lord, we are asking you to provide for your church.

39:50.749 --> 39:51.570
This is yours.

39:52.194 --> 39:53.656
In some ways, well, this is your fault.

39:54.017 --> 39:54.578
You did this.

39:55.459 --> 39:57.943
And so in that, Lord, you've got a problem with your church.

39:58.704 --> 40:03.131
And so we pray that by your grace, you would move in our hearts to respond.

40:03.171 --> 40:08.980
However, you lead us that we could be able to respond to this wonderful problem that we have.

40:09.621 --> 40:13.246
And Lord, we want to steward this movement well, but we can't do it without you.

40:13.747 --> 40:18.815
So do exceedingly abundantly beyond all we could ask or think for you and for your glory.

40:19.396 --> 40:20.978
And we'll thank you in Jesus' name.

40:21.186 --> 40:21.773
Amen.

40:21.813 --> 40:23.149
Thank you so much for coming today.

40:23.169 --> 40:23.635
God bless you.

40:23.877 --> 40:24.626
We'll see you next week.

